        <h3>Show/Hide Text in HTML</h3>
        <div>A Small Jquery script that shows/hides text. It is useful when attempting to hide text within a single div tag. I found it even more useful when my slider was reliant on switching images (using img tags), and thus pages. This would allow for text to show and hide underneath each img in the slider. However, since I've replaced the slider (on projects page) with a jquery slider I no longer needed the text. Another weakness is that the Jquery script is coded into the HTML itself, rather than at the bottom of the page.<a href=http://pastebin.com/cXs66yJZ> Go to PasteBin</a></div>
        <h3>"7Wars"</h3>
